Amber App Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 18 June 2024

1. Introduction

Welcome to Amber, a mobile application designed to enhance community safety by providing real-time alerts, enabling reports of missing people and vehicles, and keeping users informed with the latest world news. We value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share your information when you use our app.

2. Information We Collect

2.1 Personal Information

When you use Amber, we may collect the following personal information:
- Contact Information: Name, email address, and phone number.
- Location Data: Real-time geographic location to provide relevant alerts.
- User-Generated Content: Reports of missing persons, vehicles, and other incidents, including descriptions, photos, and videos.

2.2 Usage Information

We collect information about how you interact with our app, including:
- Device Information: Device type, operating system, and unique device identifiers.
- App Usage Data: Features used, time spent on the app, and other usage statistics.

3. How We Use Your Information

We use your information for the following purposes:
- To Provide Services: Deliver real-time alerts, allow you to report incidents, and provide world news updates.
- To Improve Our App: Analyze usage data to enhance the user experience and app functionality.
- To Communicate with You: Send you notifications, updates, and respond to your inquiries.
- To Ensure Safety: Verify reports and share relevant information with local authorities if necessary.

4. Sharing Your Information

We may share your information with:
- Community Members: User-generated reports may be visible to other app users.
- Service Providers: Third-party vendors who assist us in providing our services.
- Law Enforcement: Authorities if we believe it is necessary for safety, legal compliance, or protecting our users and community.

5. Data Security

We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction. However, no security system is impenetrable, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your data.

6. Your Choices

- Location Sharing: You can disable location sharing in your device settings, but this may limit the appâ€™s functionality.
- Notifications: You can opt-out of receiving notifications through your device settings.
- Account Deletion: You may request to delete your account and personal information by contacting us at project001.investment.group@gmail.com.

7. Children's Privacy

Amber is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us so we can delete it.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new policy on our app and updating the effective date. Your continued use of the app after any changes signifies your acceptance of the revised policy.

9. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:

